						<summary>

						<p>Tiruvālīśvara Temple, Central Shrine, north wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājēndra chōḻa I Year 7.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged and fragmentary. It is perfaced by the <hi rend="italic">meykkīrtti,</hi> starting with <hi rend="italic">Tirumaṉṉi vaḷara</hi> of the king.</p>						

						<p>It seems to refer to the freeing of taxes on a field (1/2) <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> in extent in favour of the temple of Śrī-Kayilāsam alias Tiruveyilvāyiluḍaiya-Paramēśvarar in Iḍaiyāṟu in Rājāśraya-vaḷanāḍu, by the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Irājēndra-siṁhachaturvēdimaṅgalam.</p>						

						</summary>
